The '''2016 Copa Sudamericana''' ({{lang-pt|'''Copa Sul-Americana 2016'''}}) was the 15th edition of the [[Copa Sudamericana]], [[South America]]'s secondary club [[association football|football]] tournament organized by [[CONMEBOL]].

The [[2016 Copa Sudamericana Finals|finals]] were originally to be played between Brazilian team [[Associação Chapecoense de Futebol|Chapecoense]] and Colombian team [[Atlético Nacional]]. However, on 28 November 2016, [[LaMia Flight 2933]], which was carrying the [[Associação Chapecoense de Futebol|Chapecoense]] squad to the first leg, crashed on the way to the [[José María Córdova International Airport]].<ref name="Gu live">{{cite web|last1=Weaver|first1=Matthew|last2=Walker|first2=Bonnie|title=Brazilian football team Chapecoense on plane that crashed in Colombia|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2016/nov/29/brazilian-team-chapecoense-onboard-plane-that-crashed-over-colombia-latest|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=76 confirmed dead in Colombian plane crash|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/11/29/americas/colombia-plane-accident/index.html|publisher=Cable News Network|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref> There were 71 fatalities, including 19 of the 22 Chapecoense players on the plane.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-38155840|title=Chapecoense plane crash: The victims, the survivors and those left behind|publisher=BBC|date=1 December 2016}}</ref> CONMEBOL immediately suspended all activities, including the scheduled final matches, in the early morning of 29 November.<ref name="Comunicado La Opinion Publica">{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/comunicado-la-opinion-publica|title=Comunicado a la opinión pública|publisher=CONMEBOL|date=29 November 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref> In light of these events, [[Atlético Nacional]] requested that CONMEBOL award the title to [[Associação Chapecoense de Futebol|Chapecoense]].<ref name="Campeón de la Sudamericana">{{cite web|title=Campeón de la Sudamericana|url=http://www.atlnacional.com.co/ultimas-noticias/campeon-de-la-sudamericana-015298|publisher=Atlético Nacional de Medellín|accessdate=29 November 2016|language=Spanish|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129192510/http://www.atlnacional.com.co/ultimas-noticias/campeon-de-la-sudamericana-015298|archive-date=2017-01-29|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> As requested, CONMEBOL awarded Chapecoense the title of the 2016 Copa Sudamericana, their first continental title, on 5 December,<ref name="Chape é declarada campeã e garante ao menos US$ 4,8 mi em premiações">{{cite web|title=Chape é declarada campeã e garante ao menos US$ 4,8 mi em premiações|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/sc/futebol/times/chapecoense/noticia/2016/12/chape-e-declarada-campea-e-garante-ao-menos-us-48-mi-em-premiacoes.html|publisher=globo.com|accessdate=5 December 2016|language=Portuguese}}</ref> while Atlético Nacional received the "CONMEBOL Centenario Fair Play" award for their gesture.<ref name="Campeón de la Sudamericana 2016">{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/conmebol-otorga-el-titulo-de-campeon-de-la-sudamericana-2016-chapecoense-y-reconoce-atletico |title=CONMEBOL otorga el título de Campeón de la Sudamericana 2016 a Chapecoense y reconoce a Atlético Nacional con el premio del Centenario de la Conmebol al Fair Play |publisher=CONMEBOL.com |date=5 December 2016 |language=Spanish |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161206042227/http://www.conmebol.com/es/conmebol-otorga-el-titulo-de-campeon-de-la-sudamericana-2016-chapecoense-y-reconoce-atletico |archivedate=6 December 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/dec/05/chapecoense-copa-sudamericana-champions|title=Chapecoense named Copa Sudamericana winners after plane crash|date=5 December 2016|work=Guardian|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref>

As winners of the 2016 Copa Sudamericana, Chapecoense earned the right to play against the winners of the [[2016 Copa Libertadores]] in the [[2017 Recopa Sudamericana]], and the winners of the [[2016 J.League Cup]] in the [[2017 Suruga Bank Championship]].<ref name="regulations">{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/sites/default/files/copa_sudamericana_2016_-_reglamento.pdf|title=Copa Sudamericana 2016&nbsp;– Reglamento|language=Spanish|publisher=CONMEBOL.com}}</ref> They also automatically qualified for the [[2017 Copa Libertadores]] group stage. [[Independiente Santa Fe|Santa Fe]] were the defending champions, but were eliminated by [[Cerro Porteño]] in the Round of 16.

==Teams==
The following 47 teams from the 10 CONMEBOL associations qualified for the tournament:
*Title holders
*Brazil: 8 berths
*Argentina: 6 berths
*All other associations: 4 berths each

The entry stage is determined as follows:
*Round of 16: Title holders
*Second stage: 14 teams (teams from Argentina and Brazil)
*First stage: 32 teams (teams from all other associations)

